oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Early Bird - 1940-0m-dd
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: WSM's Early Bird radio program (title unconfirmed), originally broadcast 1940. Hosted by Jud Collins featuring news items and pre-recorded music, sponsored by the Knoxville Fertilizer Company.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Roy Acuff
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Opening theme -- Opening statement -- Dance All Night -- Weather report -- Knoxville Fertilizer Company commercial -- Arkansas Traveler -- News report -- Knoxville Fertilizer Company commercial -- Jud Collins reads listener-submitted 'helpful hints' -- Somebody Told Me They Loved Me -- Knoxville Fertilizer Company commercial -- Closing theme (Steel Guitar Blues, Roy Acuff) -- Closing statement
